This paper discusses the evaluation of three inference methods for uncertain reasoning in the context of a large expert system for diagnosis. This topic falls under the broad category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of decision-theoretic metrics suggests a focus on decision-making and optimization, which could also place this paper in the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI). The use of expert ratings and the focus on diagnosis suggests a potential connection to databases (cs.DB) and computer engineering (cs.CE).
